The paper deals with fair division of indivisible goods, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The use of sequences of sincere choices is a common method in fair division, which is related to algorithmic decision-making (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.DS). The paper also discusses efficiency properties, which can be analyzed using machine learning techniques (cs.LG) and mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
